Adelaide Pereira da Silva (São Paulo, July 5, 1928 - São Paulo, August 8, 2021) was a Brazilian pianist, composer and painter.
She began working as a music teacher in 1960, and was also a Professor at Santa Marcelina College and Belas Artes College.
- Spring Medal - Agenor Couto de Magalhães (awarded by Sociedade Geográfica Brasileira - Brazilian Geographic Society - Campaign for ecological protection)
1965 Suite No. 1 (Shindig, Fad, Polka, Waltz, Cateretê)
Título : A Música Brasileira na atualidade, Universidade Estadual de Maringá, UEM, 2006, Maringá- PR.
Anspach, Silvia Simone PhD (2017) (Testimonial - Adelaide Pereira da Silva's niece, advanced piano student, and harmony and composition student)
